                <head>134. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 5, 1952, <persName corresp="#p_LJSJ1">James S. Lay, Jr.</persName>,
                    Executive Secretary of the National Security Council, transmitted a “Key Data
                    Book” prepared by the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Reporting Unit to
                    President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>. This briefing book
                    contained sections on the national psychological program and the foreign
                    intelligence program. For text, see <ref target="frus1952-54v02p1#pg_165">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1952–1954, volume II, Part 1,
                        pages 165</ref>–<ref target="frus1952-54v02p1#pg_181">181</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
